<br>
I'm still rearranging my quickbars, but here's my main tank one:<br>
1. Taunting Blade [blade]<br>
2. Flurry<br>
3. Fire Blade [blade, anytime]<br>
4. Spectrum Blade [blade, after Fire Blade]<br>
5. Blinding Rain [CD, after evade]<br>
6. Blizzard [CD, after Blinding Rain]<br>
7. Tornado [CD, after parrying]<br>
8. Meteor Shower [CD, after Tornado]<br>
9. Reserved for when I get Twin Star [CD, after Meteor Shower]<br>
10. Charge<br>
<br>
I really love how I now only need one button to switch from ranged to both weapons. Makes things a lot quicker/easier, especially on slower systems.<br>
<br>
I don't have any active RAs yet, although I'm starting to work towards FA/IP since that's pretty much a &quot;must have&quot;. I've got to admit, I love Mastery of Pain. Nothing is nicer than seeing both your blades crit for over 50%. It's almost like built-in Triple and Quadruple Wield. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Raeloran Twinblade</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, 42 Blademaster, Legendary Grandmaster Armorcrafter, Pellinor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sugyn>Sugyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#000000>(11/15/02 5:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=50.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Getting it Done</span><hr size=1> Your point is good but don't forget only the squeaky wheel gets oil no matter what anyone says believe me I've been around awhile.  But this is a very good idea.  I do ok in RvR and even though I don't play to much I've managed to stay in the top 25 BM's on my server.<br>
<br>
Spec Blades (common thought is blunts or pierce is better but I wanted to be a BLADE Master so have not changed) and again I do fine considering.<br>
<br>
I have seen a few sword and Board they seem to do very well blunt and board probably due even better.  Stun is devastating in RvR.<br>
<br>
I personally don't rely on positional moves in rvr, too much lag so I just have my anytime move and it's backup sorry don't recall the names.  I also have a back position style as I seem to spend alot of time chasing Albions in particular they run alot wish charge would catch them. Other than that my main toolbar is filled with the Button Masters friends FA, IP, TW, Flurry, charge (sometimes it helps if they have no speed like chasing the last tank from a dieing group)<br>
<br>
My rps went into fa and ip first must haves, had mastery of pain level III loved it want to get it again when I save up the points.<br>
<br>
Other than that find a good group to play with and a BM will do well you will be a reflection of the quality of your group.  <br>
<br>
